{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_4","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-14-prompt-rule-memo-shell.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Evolution Note — Prompt Rule Memo Shell\n\n## Plan\n\n- path: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- milestone: `Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer (complete)`\n- bounded target: add one minimal Prompt / Rule / Memo card shell without source integration\n\n## Completed\n\n- Added a dedicated `Working Memory Cards` panel to the inspector workspace\n- Added first-class visual shells for Prompt, Rule, and Memo cards with distinct type styling and explicit placeholder state\n- Kept the slice limited to card-type scaffolding and did not add file integration, editing, or workflow wiring\n\n## Failed or Deferred\n\n- Deferred source-backed cards, quick-open behavior, and workflow linkage to later slices\n\n## Decisions\n\n- Treat a visible Prompt / Rule / Memo shell as the first bounded Task 1 step needed before any source integration work\n- Move next to a Task 1 review instead of immediately attaching files to the new cards\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n```text\nContinue the codex-loop from `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`. Stay on `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md` and do one Task 1 review focused on whether the new Prompt / Rule / Memo shell is distinct enough from agent cards; if not, isolate only the smallest remaining visual distinction gap.\n```\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
